700077f-a.text:
E. 138th Street, north side, west from Willow Avenue, across Southern Boulevard. At the northwest corner of Southern Boulevard(where cans have stopped) is a new gasoline station occupying the plot seen in view 1. This plot forms the intersection of the Boulevard and Jackson Avenue, the former being on the right and the latter on the left in the first view. It appears in view 2 that the trolley tracks are being torn up.
P. L. Sperr
View 1: July 4, 1928
View 2: September 9, 1938
